owing place’ (Old English <i>sol</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived by a muddy pond, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Sole Farm in Great Bookham (Surrey).","English: nickname for someone who was unmarried, lived alone, or was lonely, from Middle English <i>sol(e)</i> ‘sole, single, lonely’ (Old French <i>sol</i>, Latin <i>solus</i> ‘alone’).","Catalan (<b>Solé</b>): variant of   Soler  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Soler","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Rafael, Carlos, Ana, Eduardo, Luis, Pedro, Jorge, Miguel, Emilio, Fernando.","Catalan:","habitational name from any of the places called (El) Soler in Catalonia (Spain), from <i>soler</i> ‘ground, floor’ (from Late Latin <i>solarium</i>, a derivative of <i>solum</i> ‘bottom’, ‘ground’)."]},{"name":"Soles","meanings":["English: habitational name from Soles Court in Nonington or Sole Street in Selling (both Kent), from the dative plural form of Old English <i>sol</i> ‘mud, slough, wallowing place’ (see   Sole  ).","English: variant of   Sole  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Catalan (<b>Solés</b>): plural form of   Soler  ."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Katherine ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Katherine Sole was born in 1410, in Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England as the daughter of John Sole. She married Thomas Corbet about 1437, in Shropshire, England. She died after 1440, in her hometown."},"et":{"1410–after 1440":"1410–pärast 1440","1410–1440":"1410–1440","1392–1420":"1392–1420","1428–1480":"1428–1480","1418–1471":"1418–1471","1385–Male":"1385–Surnud","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1385":"1385","1440":"1440","1471":"1471","after 1440":"pärast 1440","1480":"1480","1392":"1392","1418":"1418","1428":"1428","The Lee, Buckinghamshire, England":"The Lee, Buckinghamshire, England","Stanford, Shropshire, England":"Shro